				<td colspan="2"><span>Correct me if I'm wrong, but wasn't there a patch (way, waaaaay back) that allowed classes of the same type and/or level to be able to group with each other and allowed their DoTs to stack (ie two druids in RM kiting HGs) ? 
<br />
I ask because I recently came across this sitituation when a level 40 bard wished to to group with me, a level 55 bard, in Dulak. As we were both using our Tuyen's flame, poison, deases and frost songs, both with TDoK.
<br />
I understand from other threads that certain resists/ beneficial songs when played by two differents bards, the bard with higher Lvl or most AA in IM/JM negates the other bard. But understanding this and knowing there IS a patch for the Dots of same classes to stack...i can't make heads from tails <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-6.gif" border="0" alt="Sad" hspace="2" /> So any words of wisdom would help.</span></td>
