				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: duo bards Dots<a name="66786"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 13 04 6:19 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Basically, Sony has said that DoT songs will stack as long as there are no other non-stacking components in the spell, such as a magic debuff, snare, slow, etc.
<br />

<br />
What this means for bards, is that only one, I think, of our (PBAE) DoTs can stack by multiple bards.  None of the targeted DoTs will stack.
<br />

<br />
This annoys me.  I think the damage components should stack, but the other components should not.  Maybe that's too tough for their programmers to deal with.</span></td>
