				<td colspan="2"><span>The patch specifically was designed to allow stacking of DoTs that did damage only and had no other debuff components.  Frankly, Sony has now demonstrated with the AOE nerf that the damage components can be coded completely separately from the non-damage components so it is entirely possible to make our chants stack for damage and not for resist debuffs which should fulfill their intent with regard to DoTs.  Not that I expect it, but the old &quot;that would just be impossible to code&quot; argument got blown away when they demonstrated they could do it just fine when they need to.</span></td>
